Define pure helper functions in `rb-tools.el` that locate the unique regex match closest to an optional anchor line. Shell out to `ripgrep` to find the regex matches, handling no-match and ambiguous-match cases, and return the absolute line number plus the positions immediately before and after the matched line so callers can insert text on either side. Document the expected arguments (`path`, `regex`, optional `line`) and the possible errors (missing file, no matches, ambiguous matches, or non-UTF-8 files). Emphasize that the helpers expect Rust-style regexes to stay consistent with ripgrepâ€™s default flavor.